doc_summary_long: A Brazilian city's murder rate has soared by 650 per cent with 52 homicides in just three days after police officers went on strike. Military troops had to be deployed in the state of EspÃ­rito Santo after looting, rape and murders broke out on Saturday amid the industrial action. The chaos has been compared to the 2014 thriller film The Purge, where people take advantage of the absence of law and order to carry out horrific crimes.

doc_title: Brazilian city's murder rate up 650% after police strike
